LanguageData.ARA_WormholePortal_A.label: Arachne mine type
LanguageData.ARA_WormholePortal_A.description: It is a gigantic Arachne worm and constitutes the main body of the Arachne wormhole network.It can receive commands from the insects and extends its tail to a distant destination, forming an underground passage.Objects and people entering the underground passage from the head are pumped by the tunnel species and travel to the tail at high speed.Wormholes can pass in both directions.
LanguageData.Blueprint_ARA_WormholePortal_A.label: Arachne mine type (blueprint)
LanguageData.Frame_ARA_WormholePortal_A.label: Arachne tunnel type (construction)

LanguageData.ARA_WormholePortal_B.label: Arachne mine shaft exit
LanguageData.ARA_WormholePortal_B.description: This is the tail of the Arachne tunnel type, and is the exit of an underground passage formed by a long and slender body. Objects and people entering the underground passage from the tail are pumped by the tunnel type and travel at high speed to the head. Wormholes can pass in both directions.
